</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 729<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:52:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7965.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Is 200dps sustained Possible?</span><hr size=1> Let's for the sake of argument say that Black Steel is with Conjuration Spec, SCM3 and a 61+ focus earring 5.0 damage per mana. <br>
<br>
For the sake or argument, lets agree that the water pet delivers 75dps. This seems to be the closest thing to a consensus on its prowess that I have seen.<br>
<br>
To deliver 200 DPS sustained a mage would then have to make up 125. At 5.0 damage per mana, you will need about 25 mana per second rolling in, or 150/tick. I'm not going to come out and say that this is not possible, but its going to take some work. Even at only 100dps, if you had the pet DEX and otherwise buffed out the wahoozie, you are still going to have to find 20 mana per second, or 120 per tick.<br>
<br>
With things like Tranquility clocking in at 16, Bardsong at what, 15?, new transon's at 6, MC3, FT15, SP at 7, and horse meditate (about 22?), then you're only at 85 per tick (70dps), with the absolute best buff and equipment situation imaginable and 0 resists. <br>
<br>
Now we still have about 30-50 dps unaccounted for, under the best buff and ewuipment conditions imaginable.<br>
<br>
Note also that Black Steel (1540 or so damage focused) is about a 7 second cast time including gem lag and refresh. Any tricky mana games will need to take place outside that period, which means to hold 200 dps you will need to be casting it with a break between casts of a maximum of 5 seconds. You may find that if you are interveaving clicky nukes then this gap can be widened.<br>
<br>
Its not impossible based on the raw data. However, there's still a pretty big gap between the theoretical numbers and in game. Resists are yet to be accounted for, as is the need to rebuff the pet and yourself with new transons'.<br>
<br>
I'm <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>very</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> satisfied that based on the numbers presented, even an average mage in a standard Valor group (what, 50-60-70% uptime?) such a Magician could nudge and possibly hold 200 during uptime nicely. <br>
<br>
I can't imagine yet a situation in which a Mage could, for instance against an invincible, unlimited hp feared mob, deliver 200dps for an hour or 2. Its not far off, but I can't see it today. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A> at: 11/26/02 6:55:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 548<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 7:24:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7965.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Is 200dps sustained Possible?</span><hr size=1> omfg.<br>
