<br>
My argument is you could be in situations where there is absolutely ZERO downtime; as one mob dies, the puller already has another mob ready in camp which the meeles immediately start hacking into. Then we can ignore pet cannabilzation (pet is busy constantly beating on a mob) and all nuke mana must come from passive regens. Or you could be in situations where there is plenty of downtime (soloing, or a pair of casters) This shows in a way how arbitrary the within-fight DPS figure is. And in an &quot;ideal&quot; exp group, I'd be inclined to think you'd want chain pulls, otherwise the meeles are idle, wasting time. What the mage (or any caster can do) is make a less-than-ideal pull rate group slightly better by, when a mob IS in camp, killing the mob a little faster. <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
